<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-726-994  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 726 994.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computing Canada  July 19 1990 v16 n15 p8(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Plesman Publications Ltd. (Canada) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>NRC forms five new institutes. (National Research Council)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Barker, Paul.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Canada. National Research CouncilResearch and DevelopmentStrategic PlanningInformation SystemsHigh TechnologyGovernment Funding.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NRCforms five new institutesandM;The National Research Council (NRC) has realigned its organization andcreated five new institutes, one of which will focus specifically oninformation technology.andM;In announcing changes to the Ottawa-based Crown corporation, NRC presidentDr. Pierre Perron said the &quot;restructuring of part of our organization and theestablishments of new institutes follow extensive consultation with internaland external task groups.&quot;andM;The NRC's mandate is to provide a network of services, facilities, technologytransfer programs and collaborative research opportunities in support ofCanadian industry.andM;NRC spokesperson Susan Copeland said the intent of the restructure is to&quot;organize our activities in such a way that they really match the prioritiesin the real world.&quot;andM;The new institutes will focus on molecular sciences, environmental chemistry,information technology, microstructural sciences and national measurement andstandards.andM;Software engineeringandM;The IT institute's program includes work in software engineering,knowledge-based systems, sensor-based automation and systems integration.andM;Alex Mayman, the institute's director general, said the &quot;major goal is towork with Canadian industry to help enhance its competitiveness.andM;&quot;It (the restructure) is designed to give us a better focus,&quot; he said.andP;  &quot;Thepeople who are heavily involved in IT on the council will now really havetheir eye on that ball.andM;&quot;they will not have their concerns or interests diffused by also beingresponsible and involved in a variety of other areas.&quot;andO;</TEXT></DOC>